<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Slough" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Slough,</orth> 1) a place of deep mud or mire: <cit><quote>in a s. of mire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 69</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) the skin of a snake: <cit><quote>cast thy humble s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 161</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 76</bibl>. <cit><quote>with casted s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 23</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with shining checkered s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.229" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 229</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>